questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue in a Spring Boot application. A service method is marked with `@Transactional`. Inside this method, a `CompletableFuture.runAsync()` is used to perform a secondary database write to an `AuditLog` table. 

java
@Service
public class TradeService {
    @Autowired private TradeRepository tradeRepo;
    @Autowired private AuditRepository auditRepo;

    @Transactional
    public void executeTrade(Trade trade) {
        tradeRepo.save(trade); // Primary record
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            // Logic to log the trade
            auditRepo.save(new AuditLog(trade.getId(), "SUCCESS"));
        });
    }
}

Users report that while trades are saved, `AuditLog` entries are missing or throwing `TransactionRequiredException` intermittently.

You are reviewing a system where multiple `CompletableFuture` chains are used to aggregate data from 5 different microservices. You notice that during periods of high latency from one specific downstream service, the entire application becomes unresponsive, even for endpoints that do not depend on the slow service. 

java
public CompletableFuture<Data> fetchData() {
    return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> restClient.get("/slow-service"))
            .thenCombine(CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> restClient.get("/fast-service")), 
            (slow, fast) -> combine(slow, fast));
}
